If the Germania had been intended as a politica] brochum, it is impossible to understand why every indication of its character should be so absolutely wanting. We know but little, it is true, of this species of literature among the Romans, but, though extensively resorted to in the last days of the Republic, it must have been for obvious reasons ex- ceedingly rare under the Empire.
